  <p>With a new crew lining up the tunes and delving into the issues of the day, from the wee hours to 11am, Charles Darwin University?s Territory FM radio station has made a fine fresh start in 2018.<br /><br />New TFM team member David Konov, who drives the Early Mornings shift from 5am, is a long-time commercial announcer from South Australia, who spent many years in Ireland, playing a character called ?Dingo? on a breakfast show.<br /><br />Station Manager Matt Bern said he was excited by this new talent coming to Darwin.<br /><br />?I saw great potential in his voice and in his personality, and as it turns out he?s a great fit at our station because he?s got the quickness and the flow that suit the show, Matt said.<br /><br />?And along with David?s entertaining approach, we?re also fitting more music into Early Mornings to get people up and about for their day.?<br /><br />Former Breakfast Show doyenne Mel Little no longer has to rise for work at an ungodly hour as she now hosts the TFM Mornings program from 8am to 11am.<br /><br />?I?m really happy that we have our first female Mornings host in TFM?s long history,? Matt said.<br /><br />?Mel brings a fabulous fresh feel to the program, and from the feedback we?re getting by phone and on social media, it seems our audience thinks she?s great too.?<br /><br />When the new Territory FM website goes live in the next couple of months, the portal will contain a ?Health Check? community feedback page, which will provide another feedback mechanism for the station team to stay in touch with audience preferences.<br /><br /><br /><br /></p><!--
